Biography

2022: Named to Empire 8 All-Conference Third Team ... Logged career highs in points (30) and goals (21) in 18 games, which included 17 starts ... Had nine multi-point performances ... Scored a hat trick with one assist against No. 11 St. Lawrence (3/5) ... Netted four goals as part of a career-best five points against Utica (4/16) ... Netted two goals in the Empire 8 Championship game vs. Nazareth (5/7) and Fisher's NCAA Tournament win over No. 22 Catholic (5/14).

2021: Started eight of his 15 assignments at attack ... Finished the year with 19 points (14g-5a) with nine ground balls and three caused turnovers ... Scored a career-high four goals against Nazareth (4/24) ... Had three points (2g-1a) with two ground balls and one caused turnover in the Empire 8 Championship game against the Golden Flyers (5/9).

2020: Played in two games during the shortened 2020 campaign.

2019: Saw action 14 games as a sophomore ... Finished the year with 22 points (13g-9a), seven ground balls, and five caused turnovers ... First career multi-point game came with two goals and one assist against SUNY Potsdam (3/1) ... Had a season-high four points (2g-2a) against both Elmira (3/30) and Utica (4/10).

2018: Appeared in seven games as a freshman ... Amassed three points (1g-2a) with five ground balls ... Scored his first collegiate goal against Utica (4/14) ... Handed out one assist with a season-high three ground balls against Houghton (4/21).

High School: A four-year letterwinner ... Was named an Academic All-Star four times and a Section IV All-Star on the field as a senior ... Former team captain.

Personal: Brennan is the son of Rose and Chris ... Born June 29, 1999, he is majoring in Sport Management.

No stats available for the current season.
